<item>
            <title>[LU-3161] LASSERT() in lod_initialize_objects()</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-3161</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Looking at the code in lod_initialize_objects() I found the following comment and code:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;                /*
                 * XXX: assertion is left &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;for&lt;/span&gt; testing, to make
                 * sure we never process requests till configuration
                 * is completed. to be changed to -EINVAL
                 */

                lod_getref(&amp;amp;md-&amp;gt;lod_ost_descs);
                LASSERT(cfs_bitmap_check(md-&amp;gt;lod_ost_bitmap, idx));
                LASSERT(OST_TGT(md,idx));
                LASSERTF(OST_TGT(md,idx)-&amp;gt;ltd_ost, &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;idx %d\n&quot;&lt;/span&gt;, idx);
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This should be replaced by proper error handling, in case of LOV EA corruption on disk, or OST removal.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
